link:labelLink.link:label: Asset Quality Dimension
This dimension classifies assets according to the likelihood of their full economic benefits being realised.
Not Past Due 90D And Or Impaired

The data reported relates to items that have not been classified as past due for more than 90 days, and/or as impaired, in accordance with prudential standards.
Credit exposures have been past due for more than 90 days where the following criteria are met:
(1) the reporting party judges that the fair value of associated security, discounted to allow for reasonable realisation costs, is sufficient to cover the full outstanding value of the asset; and
(2) the facility is not subject to a regular repayment schedule and has remained continuously outside contractual or approved arrangements for a period of 90 days; or
(3) the facility is subject to a regular repayment schedule and: (3a) at least 90 calendar days have elapsed since the due date of a contractual payment that has not been met in full; and (3b) the total amount outside contractual arrangements is equivalent to at least 90 days' worth of contractual payments.
Prescribed Past Due 182 Days and Less Than 273 Days

The data reported relates to credit exposures where the following criteria are met:
(1) the facility is not subject to a regular repayment schedule and has remained continuously outside contractual or approved arrangements for a period of 182 days or more, but less than 273 days; or
(2) the facility is subject to a regular repayment schedule and: (2a) at least 182 calendar days, but not more than 273 days have elapsed since the due date of a contractual payment that has not been met in full; and (2b) the total amount outside contractual arrangements is equivalent to at least 182 days', but less than 273 days', worth of contractual payments.

Past Due 90 Days And Impaired

The data reported relates to items that have been classified as being past due for more than 90 days, and are classified as impaired, in accordance with prudential standards.
Credit exposures have been past due for more than 90 days where the following criteria are met:
(1) the reporting party judges that the fair value of associated security, discounted to allow for reasonable realisation costs, is sufficient to cover the full outstanding value of the asset; and
(2) the facility is not subject to a regular repayment schedule and has remained continuously outside contractual or approved arrangements for a period of 90 days; or

Past Due More Than 6 Months From Due Date And Less Than 2 Years From Event Date

The data reported relates to amounts receivable that are more than 6 months past the due date but are not outstanding on or from the second annual balance date after the date of the event giving rise to the receivable.
Not Past Due More Than 6 Months
The data reported relates to amounts receivable that are not more than 6 months past due.
Past Due on or after the 2nd Annual Balance Date after Event
The data reported relates to amounts receivable that are outstanding on or from the second annual balance date after the date of the event giving rise to the receivable.

Settlement Past Due 46 Days
The data reported relates to unsettled transactions which have been overdue for 46 business days or more.
Settlement Past Due 31 Days and Less Than 46 Days

Settlement Past Due 16 Days and Less Than 31 Days

Past Due LT90 Days

The data reported relates to credit exposures where the following criteria are met:
(1) the reporting party judges that the fair value of associated security, discounted to allow for reasonable realisation costs, is sufficient to cover the full outstanding value of the asset; and
(2) the facility is not subject to a regular repayment schedule and has remained continuously outside contractual or approved arrangements for a period not exceeding 90 days; or
(3) the facility is subject to a regular repayment schedule and: (3a) no more than 90 calendar days have elapsed since the due date of a contractual payment that has not been met in full; and (3b) the total amount outside contractual arrangements is greater than zero but equivalent to no more than 90 days' worth of contractual payments.
Past Due 90 Days

The data reported relates to credit exposures where the following criteria are met:
(1) the reporting party judges that the fair value of associated security, discounted to allow for reasonable realisation costs, is sufficient to cover the full outstanding value of the asset; and
(2) (a) the facility is not subject to a regular repayment schedule and has remained continuously outside contractual or approved arrangements for a period of 90 days; or
(b) the facility is subject to a regular repayment schedule and: (i) at least 90 calendar days have elapsed since the due date of a contractual payment that has not been met in full; and (ii) the total amount outside contractual arrangements is equivalent to at least 90 days' worth of contractual payments.
Not Impaired
The data reported relates to assets that have not been classified as impaired.
Impaired
The data reported relates to assets that have been classified as impaired.
Past Due 90 Days And Or Impaired Exceeding Exposure Limit

The data reported relates to items that have been classified as being past due for more than 90 days, and/or are classified as impaired, and where total claims covered by a single insurer exceed the reporting party's large exposure limits, as determined in accordance with prudential standards.

Illiquid
